00:39:46.497 --> 00:39:50.705
<i>I'd apologize to Ruby's dad</i>
<i>and ask for her hand.</i>


491
00:39:51.413 --> 00:39:53.163
I love Ruby and I want to...

492
00:39:56.205 --> 00:39:57.997
I've come to apologize.

493
00:39:58.288 --> 00:40:01.205
-I misbehaved that day.
-It's alright, child.


494
00:40:01.372 --> 00:40:03.372
-A tipple often does that.
-No, Daddy.


495
00:40:03.955 --> 00:40:07.122
I wasn't just drunk...
I had also done cocaine.


496
00:40:07.580 --> 00:40:13.913
Let me confess. 
The next day I did LSD.

497
00:40:14.288 --> 00:40:16.538
But I've been clean for a month.

498
00:40:19.038 --> 00:40:20.163
Congratulations!

499
00:40:25.038 --> 00:40:26.330
I'll go meet Ruby.

500
00:40:27.163 --> 00:40:29.372
-Ruby.
-Wait.


501
00:40:29.705 --> 00:40:32.372
Meet her on the 22nd
at Hotel Sun and Sand,


502
00:40:32.455 --> 00:40:34.497
with these flowers.

503
00:40:34.955 --> 00:40:36.913
-What's on the 22nd?
-Wait.


504
00:40:43.955 --> 00:40:46.205
That's for your parents.

505
00:40:46.372 --> 00:40:48.455
And that's for you. 
Write your name.

506
00:40:48.538 --> 00:40:51.372
"Ruby weds..." Who's this Rustom?

507
00:40:54.538 --> 00:40:58.455
All this for a 10 rupee bill?
I'll glue it up.


508
00:40:58.538 --> 00:41:02.497
I'm glad you tore it. 
It led us to Rustom!

509
00:41:02.580 --> 00:41:05.830
He's a doctor in New York.
Not a junkie like you.


510
00:41:07.080 --> 00:41:08.455
Daddy, let me meet Ruby--

511
00:41:14.247 --> 00:41:16.497
Then what should I call you? Old fart?

512
00:41:16.913 --> 00:41:20.497
Meet Ruby over my dead body.

513
00:41:20.580 --> 00:41:22.455
Fine, I'll wait.

514
00:41:22.538 --> 00:41:23.413
For what?

515
00:41:23.497 --> 00:41:25.163
For you to die, old fart!

516
00:41:27.997 --> 00:41:29.997
Rascal! Scoundrel!

517
00:41:30.205 --> 00:41:32.497
Get out!

518
00:41:32.580 --> 00:41:34.622
I'll break your legs, you swine.

519
00:41:37.038 --> 00:41:41.413
<i>Every addict looks for an excuse</i>
<i>to start again.</i>


520
00:41:41.580 --> 00:41:43.913
<i>My excuse was Ruby.</i>

521
00:41:53.830 --> 00:41:58.455
<i>Ruby, Ruby, Ruby</i>
<i>Let's rendezvous</i>


522
00:42:06.080 --> 00:42:09.455
<i>To have you back</i>

523
00:42:10.122 --> 00:42:13.788
<i>Your old man I'll hack</i>

524
00:42:18.163 --> 00:42:21.747
<i>It's a win-win!</i>

525
00:42:21.830 --> 00:42:25.788
<i>He gets heaven, I get you</i>

526
00:42:27.705 --> 00:42:31.163
<i>The world has no heart</i>

527
00:42:31.247 --> 00:42:34.872
<i>So leave it, old fart</i>

528
00:42:35.538 --> 00:42:39.247
<i>Goodbye, old man! 
Just die, old man!</i>

529
00:42:39.497 --> 00:42:44.830
<i>Your daughter, don't worry</i>
<i>Once you're dead, we'll marry</i>


530
00:42:45.288 --> 00:42:49.372
<i>The sincerest prayers are always granted.</i>

531
00:42:50.330 --> 00:42:54.997
<i>The old man died</i>
<i>of a massive heart attack.</i>


532
00:42:55.163 --> 00:43:00.663
<i>The news was tragic. 
But I won't lie,</i>

533
00:43:00.747 --> 00:43:02.913
<i>I was ecstatic.</i>

534
00:43:03.622 --> 00:43:08.705
<i>Ruby, Ruby, Ruby</i>
<i>Get set to rendezvous</i>


535
00:43:16.080 --> 00:43:20.997
<i>Ruby, Ruby, Ruby</i>
<i>You and I, we'll rendezvous</i>


536
00:43:22.955 --> 00:43:26.955
<i>This was my chance to win back Ruby.</i>

537
00:43:31.872 --> 00:43:36.122
<i>I had to show her,</i>
<i>I was more reliable than her fiancé.</i>


538
00:43:39.163 --> 00:43:43.538
<i>A minor problem... 
I was stoned.</i>

539
00:43:43.622 --> 00:43:45.205
Papa!

540
00:43:45.788 --> 00:43:47.788
Don't abandon us, Papa.

541
00:43:47.997 --> 00:43:51.413
-Sanju, that's not papa.
-Wake up.


542
00:43:51.872 --> 00:43:53.080
That's not papa!

543
00:43:57.538 --> 00:44:00.038
Ha! I wondered how he'd shrunk so much.

544
00:44:04.663 --> 00:44:07.413
Is this our papa?

545
00:44:09.538 --> 00:44:11.663
Papa!

546
00:44:12.163 --> 00:44:14.455
Why did you abandon us?

547
00:44:14.622 --> 00:44:16.538
Wake up. Try!

548
00:44:19.955 --> 00:44:21.455
He isn't waking up.

549
00:44:22.163 --> 00:44:24.122
Mummy, don't cry.

550
00:44:24.247 --> 00:44:26.580
Your son-in-law is with you.

551
00:44:30.163 --> 00:44:32.788
Have you read the Holy Gita?

552
00:44:33.455 --> 00:44:36.497
"Everything happens for the best."
Superb!


553
00:44:37.330 --> 00:44:39.997
"Nothing we create...

554
00:44:40.372 --> 00:44:43.288
so nothing should we mourn."

555
00:44:43.955 --> 00:44:47.163
Did you create this old man?
Gave him birth?


556
00:44:52.330 --> 00:44:53.788
Let her grieve.

557
00:44:53.872 --> 00:44:56.663
When my puppy died, 
I was bawling.

558
00:44:56.747 --> 00:45:00.538
A full-grown husband's exit
deserves howling.


559
00:45:00.622 --> 00:45:02.205
Take your time, Mummy.

560
00:45:02.288 --> 00:45:06.497
But remember, only the body perishes.

561
00:45:06.580 --> 00:45:08.330
The soul is eternal.

562
00:45:08.580 --> 00:45:10.122
Away with this body.

563
00:45:10.413 --> 00:45:12.372
Focus on the soul.

564
00:45:16.122 --> 00:45:18.372
Papa conked and you say, "All okay?"

565
00:45:19.830 --> 00:45:22.538
How shall we dispose the body?

566
00:45:22.663 --> 00:45:24.872
Bury it? Cremate it?

567
00:45:27.247 --> 00:45:29.497
God, that's not our papa.

568
00:45:29.580 --> 00:45:32.497
Move that body. 
It's freaking confusing.

569
00:45:33.080 --> 00:45:34.080
Move it.

570
00:45:34.830 --> 00:45:35.955
So, Ruby...

571
00:45:40.747 --> 00:45:42.038
What did I do?

572
00:45:46.705 --> 00:45:49.497
No one can tell it's secondhand.

573
00:45:49.913 --> 00:45:51.372
A very fair price.

574
00:45:52.205 --> 00:45:53.663
Five hundred dollars.

575
00:45:55.997 --> 00:45:57.080
What's this?

576
00:45:57.538 --> 00:45:59.163
Robbed a beggar?

577
00:45:59.247 --> 00:46:02.080
Robbed a barber! 
He cuts his own hair.

578
00:46:02.163 --> 00:46:04.247
Puts three dollars in the piggy bank.

579
00:46:04.372 --> 00:46:08.455
-Who's gonna count this?
-Call from India. It's Sanju!


580
00:46:08.538 --> 00:46:10.622
Awesome!

581
00:46:12.830 --> 00:46:18.288
Sanju, perfect timing.
I'm buying my first car.


582
00:46:18.372 --> 00:46:20.247
I need you here, bro.

583
00:46:22.830 --> 00:46:24.997
Ruby's getting married.

584
00:46:25.080 --> 00:46:26.330
<i>Please come.</i>

585
00:46:26.497 --> 00:46:29.872
-You snorting again?
-No. I swear.


586
00:46:29.955 --> 00:46:32.455
Please... come down.

587
00:46:33.080 --> 00:46:34.705
Sanju... Hello?

588
00:46:39.038 --> 00:46:41.247
Sir, no need to count.

589
00:46:41.413 --> 00:46:43.788
-The car will have to wait.
-Why?


590
00:46:43.872 --> 00:46:47.163
Need to buy a ticket to India.

591
00:46:49.913 --> 00:46:51.038
Sorry, sir.

592
00:46:51.288 --> 00:46:53.205
Didn't want the car? 
Why make me count?

593
00:47:01.872 --> 00:47:03.038
Hello, Ruby.

594
00:47:03.330 --> 00:47:06.372
I'm Kamlesh Kanhaiyalal Kapasi.
Sanju's friend.


595
00:47:07.205 --> 00:47:09.122
Sir, can you go inside?

596
00:47:09.372 --> 00:47:10.497
Take a loo break.

597
00:47:12.372 --> 00:47:15.288
-Need to discuss a private matter.
-Come.


598
00:47:19.413 --> 00:47:22.830
Whatever the matter,
say it in front of me.


599
00:47:23.247 --> 00:47:25.330
It'll upset you.

600
00:47:25.580 --> 00:47:28.622
Take a stroll outside. 
Lovely weather.

601
00:47:32.705 --> 00:47:34.080
Really?

602
00:47:37.622 --> 00:47:39.830
Then name Ruby's favorite animal.

603
00:47:45.830 --> 00:47:47.122
You live in New York?

604
00:47:47.705 --> 00:47:51.247
Ask any jeweler there...

605
00:47:51.455 --> 00:47:53.663
They'll all say... "Penguin".

606
00:47:55.080 --> 00:47:56.538
-Know why?
-Why?


607
00:47:56.663 --> 00:48:00.247
For a month, Sanju hopped
from jeweler to jeweler


608
00:48:00.413 --> 00:48:04.372
for a wedding necklace
with a penguin pendant.


609
00:48:04.913 --> 00:48:06.455
And finally got it!

610
00:48:06.580 --> 00:48:08.455
But when he returned to India,

611
00:48:08.580 --> 00:48:11.163
he discovered that you were engaged.

612
00:48:11.872 --> 00:48:15.163
He was shattered, so took to drugs again.

613
00:48:15.247 --> 00:48:17.497
But yesterday, he braved up.

614
00:48:17.580 --> 00:48:19.788
Flushed all the drugs down the drain.

615
00:48:20.247 --> 00:48:22.622
Swore never to touch them again.

616
00:48:22.705 --> 00:48:25.455
He prayed, "Lord, bring Ruby back."

617
00:48:26.288 --> 00:48:28.163
Sanju's back.

618
00:48:28.663 --> 00:48:29.872
Can you come back?

619
00:48:31.830 --> 00:48:34.288
The wedding date, venue... it's all set.

620
00:48:34.372 --> 00:48:36.622
Nothing changes, except the groom.

621
00:48:36.705 --> 00:48:38.622
The wedding cards have been printed.

622
00:48:38.705 --> 00:48:41.830
We'll put a "Sanju" sticker
over your name.


623
00:48:41.913 --> 00:48:43.455
Don't sweat the small stuff.

624
00:48:48.830 --> 00:48:52.830
Ruby, in America
there'll be no house help.


625
00:48:53.038 --> 00:48:55.288
You'll be cleaning, mopping, washing...

626
00:48:55.455 --> 00:48:57.997
Imagine washing his sweaty underpants!

627
00:48:59.705 --> 00:49:01.247
I told you, you'd be upset.

628
00:49:01.330 --> 00:49:05.163
Sanju will be at the Marriage Registrar's,
tomorrow at 4 p.m.


629
00:49:19.955 --> 00:49:21.747
Mister, what's her favorite food?

630
00:49:24.122 --> 00:49:26.497
Waffles. Sanju knows.

631
00:49:28.330 --> 00:49:29.705
Her favorite film?

632
00:49:30.913 --> 00:49:32.330
<i>Mary Poppins.</i>

633
00:49:32.455 --> 00:49:35.372
Sanju knows. You have no clue.

634
00:49:35.913 --> 00:49:37.288
Ruby, 4 p.m. tomorrow.

635
00:49:37.705 --> 00:49:39.830
The Marriage Registrar's office.

636
00:49:55.788 --> 00:49:57.872
Where did you get money for this?

637
00:49:58.205 --> 00:50:00.330
Your wallet, checks... 
They're with me.

638
00:50:03.080 --> 00:50:05.372
The wedding necklace...

639
00:50:05.497 --> 00:50:06.580
What about it?

640
00:50:06.705 --> 00:50:09.163
I sold it to God.

641
00:50:20.580 --> 00:50:23.955
-Where's he?
-He isn't home.


642
00:50:24.038 --> 00:50:25.913
<i>Woo-hoo!</i>

643
00:50:39.330 --> 00:50:43.247
I wait at the Registrar's office
and you get stoned here?


644
00:50:43.788 --> 00:50:47.497
No sweat. We'll marry tomorrow.

645
00:50:51.038 --> 00:50:54.872
You'd flushed the drugs!
Fished them out again?


646
00:51:01.372 --> 00:51:04.163
Where's the wedding necklace?

647
00:51:05.788 --> 00:51:07.372
Where is it?

648
00:51:07.872 --> 00:51:10.163
Where's the bloody necklace?

649
00:51:19.372 --> 00:51:20.788
The wedding necklace.

650
00:51:46.538 --> 00:51:48.330
Please wait, Ruby.

651
00:51:50.538 --> 00:51:52.455
I'm sorry...

652
00:51:53.247 --> 00:51:54.247
Yuck.

653
00:51:54.497 --> 00:51:58.163
He's not in his senses.
Won't remember a thing tomorrow!


654
00:51:58.247 --> 00:52:01.788
I swear, he did buy the wedding necklace.

655
00:52:04.080 --> 00:52:06.372
He's too far gone

656
00:52:06.663 --> 00:52:09.288
and to expect you'll
hang on is not right.

657
00:52:10.788 --> 00:52:14.163
You move on, I'm with him.

658
00:52:24.705 --> 00:52:25.955
Kamlesh.

659
00:52:26.330 --> 00:52:27.288
Yes, Ruby.

660
00:52:27.372 --> 00:52:29.538
Don't ever tell him what he did.

661
00:52:30.080 --> 00:52:31.788
He'll be devastated.

662
00:52:32.080 --> 00:52:33.413
Tell him...

663
00:52:34.538 --> 00:52:36.997
that rotten Ruby never showed up.

664
00:52:56.830 --> 00:52:58.497
You've been drinking?

665
00:52:58.622 --> 00:53:02.455
What I wanna say needs courage.

666
00:53:03.288 --> 00:53:05.872
So I downed a couple.

667
00:53:06.747 --> 00:53:07.997
Tell me.

668
00:53:09.538 --> 00:53:12.705
Your son will die before your wife!

669
00:53:13.205 --> 00:53:16.372
-He can't handle his life.
-Why?


670
00:53:17.122 --> 00:53:20.122
He sees you nursing your ailing wife.

671
00:53:20.830 --> 00:53:25.455
Any responsibility at home,
film industry, society...


672
00:53:25.830 --> 00:53:28.413
he sees you never shirk it.

673
00:53:31.205 --> 00:53:33.080
And your son...

674
00:53:34.497 --> 00:53:36.955
He's an ordinary guy.

675
00:53:37.247 --> 00:53:40.372
No goals, no purpose in life.

676
00:53:40.455 --> 00:53:45.122
He says,
"There are three things to life, bro."


677
00:53:46.413 --> 00:53:49.413
"C, B, S."

678
00:53:50.288 --> 00:53:53.538
"Chew, brew and scr..."

679
00:53:59.288 --> 00:54:02.913
The problem is, you
want him to be you!

680
00:54:04.830 --> 00:54:05.997
He's buried...

681
00:54:06.372 --> 00:54:09.788
buried under the weight of your legacy!

682
00:54:10.288 --> 00:54:14.205
He knows, however hard he toils,
he can never be as great.


683
00:54:14.288 --> 00:54:17.163
So, he doesn't even try.

684
00:54:19.247 --> 00:54:22.205
Feels a hero with nobodies like me.

685
00:54:22.288 --> 00:54:25.830
"Yo, Kamli...", "Hey, Kamli..."

686
00:54:29.705 --> 00:54:32.747
What should I do, Kamlesh?

687
00:54:32.830 --> 00:54:34.372
Sir, you...

688
00:54:39.080 --> 00:54:40.913
Just be his friend.

689
00:54:40.997 --> 00:54:42.913
Sit with him.

690
00:54:43.330 --> 00:54:44.747
Drink with him.

691
00:54:44.830 --> 00:54:47.497
Use a few cuss words, and say...

692
00:54:47.580 --> 00:54:52.372
"Sonny, it's okay to be ordinary."

693
00:54:52.872 --> 00:54:55.038
"You don't have to be Sunil Dutt."

694
00:54:55.122 --> 00:54:57.913
"It's okay to be Sanjay Dutt.”

695
00:54:58.413 --> 00:55:01.997
Sir, please save him.

696
00:55:03.830 --> 00:55:04.913
If he dies,

697
00:55:04.997 --> 00:55:08.788
whom will I tell, "Let go my twins"?

698
00:55:11.830 --> 00:55:14.497
Please, sir, save him.

699
00:55:17.413 --> 00:55:19.080
Save him.

700
00:55:39.163 --> 00:55:41.372
I showed the distributors your film.

701
00:55:41.497 --> 00:55:46.538
They went crazy...
"What a freaking actor!"


702
00:55:52.122 --> 00:55:53.872
Has mom seen the posters?

703
00:55:54.163 --> 00:55:55.997
She's in hospital.

704
00:55:56.538 --> 00:55:57.455
What happened?

705
00:55:58.872 --> 00:56:01.163
She slipped into a coma again.

706
00:56:01.247 --> 00:56:04.997
-I just met her yesterday!
-No, day before.


707
00:56:05.080 --> 00:56:08.913
You've woken up after two days. It's okay.

708
00:56:13.247 --> 00:56:15.038
I've spoken to the doctors.

709
00:56:15.122 --> 00:56:18.247
They recommend a rehab center in America.

710
00:56:18.580 --> 00:56:19.455
Ready?

711
00:56:20.205 --> 00:56:21.205
No!

712
00:56:21.455 --> 00:56:22.955
Please don't send me there, Dad.

713
00:56:23.122 --> 00:56:24.830
Just a few days, sonny.

714
00:56:25.330 --> 00:56:26.497
No.

715
00:56:30.788 --> 00:56:34.205
Come out. We won't send you anywhere.

716
00:56:34.288 --> 00:56:37.122
I had one cigarette, you packed me off
to boarding school.


717
00:56:37.205 --> 00:56:40.038
I was just six.
Couldn't even tie my shoelaces.


718
00:56:40.122 --> 00:56:41.413
I missed mom.

719
00:56:43.330 --> 00:56:44.247
Please come out.

720
00:56:45.497 --> 00:56:47.288
I won't go anywhere.

721
00:56:47.580 --> 00:56:50.080
I'll stay with mom in the hospital!

722
00:56:55.080 --> 00:56:58.080
<i>Dad agreed... on one condition.</i>

723
00:56:58.205 --> 00:57:01.497
<i>That I wouldn't do drugs in the hospital.</i>

724
00:57:01.788 --> 00:57:03.205
<i>And I promised.</i>

725
00:57:03.830 --> 00:57:06.247
<i>I started spending</i>
<i>every night at the hospital.</i>


726
00:57:06.747 --> 00:57:09.372
<i>I'd stare at mom for hours.</i>

727
00:57:09.705 --> 00:57:12.163
<i>I'd hold her hand and talk to her.</i>

728
00:57:12.538 --> 00:57:14.580
The premiere's next week.

729
00:57:14.747 --> 00:57:16.080
Won't you come?

730
00:57:16.538 --> 00:57:17.538
Get up, Mom.

731
00:57:17.872 --> 00:57:19.705
You gotta see me act.

732
00:57:20.080 --> 00:57:21.997
You'll be proud, Mom.

733
00:57:23.080 --> 00:57:24.038
Mom.

734
00:57:26.538 --> 00:57:27.747
<i>Then one day...</i>

735
00:57:27.955 --> 00:57:29.330
<i>I couldn't resist.</i>

736
00:57:48.080 --> 00:57:49.455
<i>Sanju...</i>

737
00:58:55.622 --> 00:58:57.747
<i>Mom never saw my film.</i>

738
00:58:58.497 --> 00:59:02.163
<i>She died three days before the premiere.</i>

739
00:59:02.747 --> 00:59:04.080
<i>She'd left a note...</i>

740
00:59:04.163 --> 00:59:07.080
<i>"Even if I'm gone,
the show must go on."</i>

741
00:59:14.538 --> 00:59:20.122
<i>They call me Rocky</i>
<i>Yes, my name is Rocky!</i>


742
00:59:21.330 --> 00:59:28.122
<i>Friend and foe</i>
<i>To both I say hello</i>


743
00:59:28.997 --> 00:59:35.580
<i>Friend and foe</i>
