We're going to the Supreme Court.


1222
01:42:22.622 --> 01:42:23.455
You get better.

1223
01:42:24.038 --> 01:42:27.247
Why are you lying?

1224
01:42:28.663 --> 01:42:32.830
I know my bail's rejected.
I've been in for six months.


1225
01:42:32.913 --> 01:42:35.747
You know the Prime Minister...
the President... speak to them.


1226
01:42:35.830 --> 01:42:39.705
What have I done?
Killed anyone? Fire a bullet?


1227
01:42:40.372 --> 01:42:42.247
Just kept a gun, for your protection!

1228
01:42:42.705 --> 01:42:44.122
My protection?

1229
01:42:46.163 --> 01:42:50.622
I'd rather you shot me with that gun!

1230
01:42:57.872 --> 01:42:59.080
He'll never appreciate me.

1231
01:43:00.788 --> 01:43:05.747
Praises my sisters all the time...
"Ace! Well played!"


1232
01:43:07.580 --> 01:43:09.247
I want to die.

1233
01:43:09.747 --> 01:43:10.580
Please help me.

1234
01:43:17.163 --> 01:43:18.663
There's cyanide in the tea.

1235
01:43:21.872 --> 01:43:22.788
Drink up.

1236
01:43:29.247 --> 01:43:30.538
Vodka in the tea?

1237
01:43:30.622 --> 01:43:32.955
Now chill! Don't blabber about dying.

1238
01:43:33.038 --> 01:43:34.455
Think of your dad!

1239
01:43:34.872 --> 01:43:36.997
He strives from dawn to dusk
for your bail.


1240
01:43:37.163 --> 01:43:40.955
Begs lawyers, politicians, cops...

1241
01:43:41.413 --> 01:43:44.538
Sleeps on the floor
'cause you have no bed.


1242
01:43:44.872 --> 01:43:47.122
Doesn't use the fan
'cause you don't have one.


1243
01:43:47.205 --> 01:43:50.955
People call him, "Terrorist's pop."

1244
01:43:51.955 --> 01:43:54.997
You've twisted his twins,
now spare him your suicide!


1245
01:43:55.497 --> 01:43:57.872
Fight! You'll definitely get bail.

1246
01:44:06.872 --> 01:44:08.163
Once out of prison...

1247
01:44:08.997 --> 01:44:10.955
get a sexy girlfriend.

1248
01:44:11.705 --> 01:44:15.247
I'll get you drunk and bam-bam her!

1249
01:44:15.830 --> 01:44:17.330
Then, we're even.

1250
01:44:19.247 --> 01:44:22.663
"I want to die." Enough! 
You're a tiger.

1251
01:44:23.288 --> 01:44:26.038
"Rorr"... come on.

1252
01:44:26.580 --> 01:44:27.997
"Rorr!"

1253
01:44:37.205 --> 01:44:39.247
<i>He spent 452 days in prison.</i>

1254
01:44:40.080 --> 01:44:42.455
<i>The Supreme Court finally</i>
<i>granted him bail.</i>


1255
01:44:43.205 --> 01:44:45.580
<i>But his name was now</i>
<i>synonymous with the word...</i>


1256
01:44:48.705 --> 01:44:51.247
<i>The public and the press hated him.</i>

1257
01:44:51.913 --> 01:44:55.622
<i>He was being tried under the Terror Act...</i>

1258
01:44:55.955 --> 01:44:58.247
<i>he feared his bail would be canceled.</i>

1259
01:44:59.080 --> 01:45:02.288
<i>His only hope was political intervention.</i>

1260
01:45:02.788 --> 01:45:06.788
<i>An influential minister in the capital</i>
<i>agreed to meet him.</i>


1261
01:45:07.205 --> 01:45:08.080
Hello, sir.

1262
01:45:09.205 --> 01:45:12.580
Come... sit.

1263
01:45:13.330 --> 01:45:14.872
How's daddy?

1264
01:45:15.538 --> 01:45:16.580
He has a fever.

1265
01:45:16.663 --> 01:45:18.455
Very good...

1266
01:45:19.872 --> 01:45:21.705
What brings you here?

1267
01:45:22.663 --> 01:45:23.997
Sir, I'll be honest.

1268
01:45:25.205 --> 01:45:26.247
I did possess a gun.

1269
01:45:27.080 --> 01:45:29.497
I should be tried under the Arms Act.

1270
01:45:30.205 --> 01:45:32.413
But they've slapped me
with the Terror Act.


1271
01:45:33.788 --> 01:45:36.705
If I was involved in the bomb blasts,

1272
01:45:36.913 --> 01:45:38.372
would I return to India?

1273
01:45:38.872 --> 01:45:41.080
I could've run away from Mauritius.

1274
01:45:41.622 --> 01:45:43.455
Taken asylum in another country.

1275
01:45:53.080 --> 01:45:55.372
-He's dozed off!
-Speak louder.


1276
01:45:58.080 --> 01:46:01.955
Sir, I got a gun because
I feared a mob attack.


1277
01:46:06.872 --> 01:46:10.705
<i>If the minister really slept</i>
<i>or play acted to avoid us</i>


1278
01:46:10.788 --> 01:46:12.705
<i>is still a mystery.</i>

1279
01:46:17.663 --> 01:46:18.747
How's daddy?

1280
01:46:20.455 --> 01:46:23.455
-He has a fever.
-Very good...


1281
01:46:25.205 --> 01:46:26.705
What brings you here?

1282
01:46:28.288 --> 01:46:31.372
Our legs brought us here...
we'll go back swimming.


1283
01:46:31.455 --> 01:46:33.913
Very good...

1284
01:46:34.122 --> 01:46:36.372
Let me know if I can help.

1285
01:46:36.955 --> 01:46:39.080
<i>It was evident, we were on our own.</i>

1286
01:46:39.872 --> 01:46:42.997
<i>I decided that until Sanju was cleared</i>
<i>of terror charges,</i>


1287
01:46:43.330 --> 01:46:46.788
<i>I'd be by his side. 
But the next day...</i>

1288
01:46:54.872 --> 01:46:55.913
Babu, where's Sanju?

1289
01:46:56.580 --> 01:46:57.830
In the preview theatre.

1290
01:47:08.622 --> 01:47:10.747
No one goes in. Mr. 
Dutt's orders.

1291
01:47:10.830 --> 01:47:16.913
Tell the Court, you knew about
the bomb blast conspiracy.


1292
01:47:19.705 --> 01:47:20.872
Kamlesh,

1293
01:47:21.205 --> 01:47:22.455
please wait outside.

1294
01:47:38.122 --> 01:47:39.122
Where are you going?

1295
01:47:39.955 --> 01:47:42.413
FBI raided my office.

1296
01:47:43.163 --> 01:47:44.163
Why?

1297
01:47:49.622 --> 01:47:51.830
What's that got to do with the FBI?

1298
01:47:53.080 --> 01:47:55.830
My company works with
the American government.


1299
01:47:56.163 --> 01:47:58.413
Now they'll investigate our association.

1300
01:47:59.038 --> 01:48:00.997
Terror charges freak them out.

1301
01:48:04.288 --> 01:48:05.288
Sorry, buddy.

1302
01:48:06.330 --> 01:48:08.080
I've put you through all this...

1303
01:48:09.705 --> 01:48:14.080
-Call me when you get there.
-No... my phone will be tapped.


1304
01:48:15.913 --> 01:48:18.288
We must disconnect for a few years.

1305
01:48:21.038 --> 01:48:24.038
Don't worry. I understand. Go...

1306
01:48:25.663 --> 01:48:27.872
Hey, Kamli. You're a tiger.

1307
01:48:36.330 --> 01:48:37.538
Let's go.

1308
01:48:47.955 --> 01:48:50.330
First time ever I lied to Sanju.

1309
01:48:50.413 --> 01:48:52.205
I can be friends with an addict.

1310
01:48:52.997 --> 01:48:58.747
Even with a guy who slept with my girl.
But with a terrorist? I'm no fool!


1311
01:49:01.372 --> 01:49:04.247
Every time I drink, I miss him...

1312
01:49:04.872 --> 01:49:06.288
yearn to call him.

1313
01:49:07.705 --> 01:49:09.580
Then I remind myself...

1314
01:49:10.497 --> 01:49:13.788
there was a truck full of RDX
at his house.


1315
01:49:13.872 --> 01:49:15.663
He's a bloody terrorist!

1316
01:49:17.788 --> 01:49:19.038
Are we done?

1317
01:49:22.913 --> 01:49:24.038
<i>Mail from Winnie.</i>

1318
01:49:24.580 --> 01:49:25.705
Where's she?

1319
01:49:26.788 --> 01:49:27.622
America.

1320
01:49:28.997 --> 01:49:30.163
She won't write the book.

1321
01:49:33.663 --> 01:49:36.288
<i>Sanjay Dutt was given 30 days</i>
<i>to surrender.</i>


1322
01:49:36.455 --> 01:49:37.788
<i>That time is over.</i>

1323
01:49:37.955 --> 01:49:42.205
<i>He's on his way to prison.</i>

1324
01:49:42.788 --> 01:49:43.747
<i>Clothes off.</i>

1325
01:49:44.747 --> 01:49:45.913
Raise your hands.

1326
01:49:48.747 --> 01:49:49.955
Turn.

1327
01:49:54.122 --> 01:49:55.122
Bend.

1328
01:49:57.705 --> 01:49:58.872
Cough.

1329
01:49:59.455 --> 01:50:00.622
Harder.

1330
01:50:40.080 --> 01:50:43.038
You dropped Sanju's story
for a book on museums?


1331
01:50:45.580 --> 01:50:49.205
-Museums don't lie.
-Nor did Sanju.


1332
01:50:49.580 --> 01:50:53.455
But a news report
became your gospel truth.


1333
01:50:56.038 --> 01:50:57.038
What's this?

1334
01:50:57.705 --> 01:51:00.997
Prison has a community radio
for prisoners' reform.


1335
01:51:01.413 --> 01:51:03.830
Sanju hosts a show.

1336
01:51:04.330 --> 01:51:06.747
He wants you to hear this episode.

1337
01:51:06.955 --> 01:51:08.497
Took great pains to smuggle it out.

1338
01:51:12.997 --> 01:51:14.205
My number.

1339
01:51:14.538 --> 01:51:16.538
You'll need it after you're done.

1340
01:51:30.913 --> 01:51:33.205
<i>Howdy, Yerwada!</i>

1341
01:51:33.288 --> 01:51:37.830
This is your buddy, Sanju!

1342
01:51:41.872 --> 01:51:46.372
Today's topic is "newspapers."

1343
01:51:47.038 --> 01:51:50.080
There were no newspapers 400 years ago.

1344
01:51:50.413 --> 01:51:52.205
News traveled word of mouth.

1345
01:51:52.288 --> 01:51:54.455
<i>Then, someone printed the first newspaper.</i>

1346
01:51:54.580 --> 01:51:57.913
<i>Soon, selling news became big business.</i>

1347
01:51:58.288 --> 01:52:04.830
Today, India has 105,437
registered publications,


1348
01:52:05.288 --> 01:52:08.413
thousands of radio stations,
TV channels and the internet.


1349
01:52:09.122 --> 01:52:11.663
And they're in a rat race...

1350
01:52:12.580 --> 01:52:14.705
fighting for readership.

1351
01:52:15.122 --> 01:52:18.413
More readers means more money from ads.

1352
01:52:19.497 --> 01:52:23.538
And how do you lure readers?
With the truth?


1353
01:52:24.913 --> 01:52:25.830
No.

1354
01:52:26.622 --> 01:52:29.497
With news that's spicy!

1355
01:52:30.580 --> 01:52:33.497
And how do you do that?

1356
01:52:34.080 --> 01:52:35.955
Easy! With a question mark.

1357
01:52:38.663 --> 01:52:44.663
When I was on bail,
these question marks were on my tail.


1358
01:52:44.747 --> 01:52:46.413
SANJU IN A BRAWL?

1359
01:52:51.372 --> 01:52:53.163
SANJU SOZZLED?

1360
01:52:56.288 --> 01:52:59.913
<i>Dad decided to fight back.</i>

1361
01:52:59.997 --> 01:53:02.705
Mr. Dutt, what a surprise!

1362
01:53:02.788 --> 01:53:04.830
How many pages does your paper have?

1363
01:53:05.747 --> 01:53:07.705
-Twenty four.
-Cut it down to eight.


1364
01:53:08.747 --> 01:53:11.747
Then you won't need
fake news to fill pages.


1365
01:53:12.413 --> 01:53:13.747
Please come.

1366
01:53:15.747 --> 01:53:20.997
If our reportage bothers you, sue us.

1367
01:53:22.622 --> 01:53:24.538
How can I fight you?

1368
01:53:24.622 --> 01:53:26.247
You have James Bond with you.

1369
01:53:27.122 --> 01:53:28.038
James Bond?

1370
01:53:28.122 --> 01:53:31.122
James Bond has a license to kill.

1371
01:53:31.413 --> 01:53:34.288
He has legal immunity.

1372
01:53:34.497 --> 01:53:37.163
Similarly, you have these question marks.

1373
01:53:37.497 --> 01:53:40.330
In Court, you'll state,
"This isn't confirmed news."


1374
01:53:40.413 --> 01:53:43.747
"Just speculation.
Don't miss the question mark."


1375
01:53:43.830 --> 01:53:45.580
"According to sources..."

1376
01:53:48.788 --> 01:53:50.997
These are your James Bond!

1377
01:53:56.788 --> 01:54:00.997
<i>Bandu Boss, I'll be there. 
Tell me when.</i>

1378
01:54:01.163 --> 01:54:04.247
<i>Last day of Ganesha festival.</i>

1379
01:54:04.580 --> 01:54:06.080
<i>Done.</i>

1380
01:54:08.288 --> 01:54:12.913
Your son graces events by gangsters.

1381
01:54:13.580 --> 01:54:16.497
Cops have 60 such phone taps.

1382
01:54:16.913 --> 01:54:20.413
He's not focused on work.
His last 12 films tanked.


1383
01:54:20.913 --> 01:54:26.497
His bail can be revoked.
In short, he's finished!


1384
01:54:27.080 --> 01:54:30.830
Then state that with conviction.

1385
01:54:31.955 --> 01:54:35.163
Put a full stop. 
Not a question mark.

1386
01:54:49.622 --> 01:54:53.663
Mr. Editor, don't write his obituary yet.

1387
01:54:53.747 --> 01:54:55.663
My son will rise again.

1388
01:54:56.288 --> 01:54:59.455
I'll prove you wrong.

1389
01:54:59.788 --> 01:55:01.955
I'm around, and so are you.

1390
01:55:02.122 --> 01:55:03.330
We'll meet again.

1391
01:55:08.955 --> 01:55:13.997
<i>A lousy editor writing me off</i>
<i>was unacceptable to dad.</i>


1392
01:55:14.580 --> 01:55:18.705
<i>He resolved to get
my life back on track.</i>

1393
01:55:18.872 --> 01:55:23.247
If you hobnob with gangsters,
won't the press hound you?


1394
01:55:23.913 --> 01:55:25.330
Gangster? Who, Dad?

1395
01:55:27.788 --> 01:55:29.038
Bandu Boss.

1396
01:55:30.122 --> 01:55:32.122
Aren't you attending his event?

1397
01:55:33.913 --> 01:55:37.372
What's the option? 
They're dangerous.

1398
01:55:38.247 --> 01:55:39.455
Don't go.

1399
01:55:39.788 --> 01:55:42.913
They'll kill me. 
They shot Gulshan Kumar.

1400
01:55:43.163 --> 01:55:46.080
-Fired at Rakesh Roshan.
-Don't go, sonny.


1401
01:55:46.455 --> 01:55:50.205
If the snoopy press
ensures my safety, I won't go.


1402
01:56:11.413 --> 01:56:12.663
Why are we here, Dad?

1403
01:56:12.747 --> 01:56:15.872
When I was to marry your mom,

1404
01:56:16.080 --> 01:56:21.122
a notorious don... 
Mastan, got livid.

1405
01:56:21.913 --> 01:56:24.705
"Nargis is the pride
of the Muslim community."


1406
01:56:25.372 --> 01:56:28.372
"If a Hindu marries her,
we'll slaughter him."


1407
01:56:28.872 --> 01:56:30.955
I called him and said...

1408
01:56:32.122 --> 01:56:35.622
"Let's meet and talk."

1409
01:56:35.788 --> 01:56:40.580
He agreed. 1 a.m... right here.

1410
01:56:41.997 --> 01:56:44.663
-You came here alone?
-No.


1411
01:56:45.163 --> 01:56:47.080
My Master was with me.

1412
01:56:47.622 --> 01:56:49.955
-Which one?
-Sahir Ludhianvi.


1413
01:56:50.538 --> 01:56:53.538
I reached an hour earlier.

1414
01:56:53.955 --> 01:56:57.580
I let Sahir's song
play in my mind on loop.


1415
01:56:58.205 --> 01:57:04.038
When the don arrived,
I said, "I love Nargis deeply."


1416
01:57:04.872 --> 01:57:06.413
"I want to marry her."

1417
01:57:06.913 --> 01:57:09.163
"And I'll keep her happy forever."

1418
01:57:09.663 --> 01:57:13.580
"If to love someone is wrong, shoot me."

1419
01:57:13.872 --> 01:57:16.997
"If right, give me a hug."

1420
01:57:17.580 --> 01:57:19.038
On our wedding day,

1421
01:57:19.413 --> 01:57:21.622
the biggest bouquet...

1422
01:57:23.038 --> 01:57:24.122
came from Mastan!

1423
01:57:26.705 --> 01:57:29.663
-What song was it, Dad?
-Will you sing it?


1424
01:57:30.705 --> 01:57:32.705
Sing along with me.

1425
01:57:35.330 --> 01:57:38.955
<i>Vicious or vile, let no power</i>

1426
01:57:39.038 --> 01:57:41.580
<i>Ever let you cower</i>

1427
01:57:41.788 --> 01:57:45.080
-Dad, not here.
-Come on, catch the beat.


1428
01:57:46.080 --> 01:57:49.747
<i>Vicious or vile, let no power</i>

1429
01:57:49.872 --> 01:57:52.747
<i>Ever let you cower</i>

1430
01:57:53.372 --> 01:58:00.372
<i>Look evil in the eye</i>
<i>Your head held high</i>


1431
01:58:00.872 --> 01:58:07.663
<i>So what if this be your last breath?</i>

1432
01:58:08.455 --> 01:58:15.163
<i>Rejoice, you never died before your death!</i>

1433
01:58:24.288 --> 01:58:30.580
Sonny, go... let Bandu Boss have it.

1434
01:58:30.997 --> 01:58:32.830
He'll never call again.

1435
01:58:32.913 --> 01:58:36.663
<i>Break</i>

1436
01:58:36.747 --> 01:58:40.622
<i>Every shackle</i>

1437
01:58:42.705 --> 01:58:48.622
<i>Smith each into</i>

1438
01:58:49.580 --> 01:58:53.080
<i>A sword</i>

1439
01:58:54.455 --> 01:58:55.497
Stop!

1440
01:58:59.830 --> 01:59:01.038
Hey, the great Sanju!

1441
01:59:01.163 --> 01:59:03.205
Boss, look who's here.

1442
01:59:04.788 --> 01:59:06.122
The star!

1443
01:59:06.747 --> 01:59:08.497
Welcome!

1444
01:59:09.205 --> 01:59:12.705
No calendar at home?
You're ten days early!


1445
01:59:12.788 --> 01:59:16.580
Welcome... sit.

1446
01:59:20.372 --> 01:59:22.747
May I speak in private?

1447
01:59:22.830 --> 01:59:23.997
In private?

1448
01:59:24.580 --> 01:59:26.413
They're family.

1449
01:59:27.872 --> 01:59:29.372
Close your ears.

1450
01:59:31.413 --> 01:59:35.538
We reject condoms
and eject large families.


1451
01:59:36.663 --> 01:59:38.497
Now tell me.

1452
01:59:41.122 --> 01:59:43.163
I can't attend the Ganesha festival.

1453
01:59:45.413 --> 01:59:46.997
Are you sloshed?

1454
01:59:47.413 --> 01:59:49.497
I've already announced to the world.

1455
01:59:49.622 --> 01:59:51.705
My parents are joining, too.

1456
01:59:51.830 --> 01:59:54.497
I too have a father. 
He disapproves.

1457
01:59:57.122 --> 01:59:59.330
He approves when you meet
the gangs in Dubai?


1458
02:00:00.413 --> 02:00:03.247
Did I have a choice? I was scared.

1459
02:00:05.538 --> 02:00:07.497
You ain't scared of me?

1460
02:00:08.622 --> 02:00:10.663
Boys, show him fear.

1461
02:00:32.372 --> 02:00:34.705
Wanna see your brains?

1462
02:00:37.872 --> 02:00:40.955
Blow them out, but first... hear me out.

1463
02:00:42.580 --> 02:00:47.622
If I attend your event,
the press will print...


1464
02:00:47.913 --> 02:00:49.080
"Sanju
-Gangsters Romance."

1465
02:00:49.622 --> 02:00:53.830
If I don't attend, "Gang kills Sanju."

1466
02:00:54.080 --> 02:00:56.122
Either ways, it'll make headlines.

1467
02:00:56.330 --> 02:01:00.330
But, the second headline
won't shame my dad.


1468
02:01:00.913 --> 02:01:02.538
He'll cry gallons.

1469
02:01:03.163 --> 02:01:06.872
But when he faces the world,
his head will be held high.


1470
02:01:07.538 --> 02:01:09.247
Not bowed down in shame.

1471
02:01:11.455 --> 02:01:14.955
If this makes sense... fine.

1472
02:01:18.288 --> 02:01:19.413
If not, shoot me.

1473
02:01:22.955 --> 02:01:25.122
-Boss...
-Shut up!


1474
02:01:31.330 --> 02:01:32.705
I'll leave now.

1475
02:01:33.497 --> 02:01:35.788
If I've overstepped, I'm sorry.

1476
02:01:59.663 --> 02:02:02.663
<i>Bandu Boss never called.</i>

1477
02:02:03.747 --> 02:02:05.497
<i>But he showed up!</i>

1478
02:02:12.080 --> 02:02:13.997
It's a family tradition.

1479
02:02:14.413 --> 02:02:16.705
No murders during the Ganesha fest.

1480
02:02:17.372 --> 02:02:19.330
Decided to kill you after the fest.

1481
02:02:19.788 --> 02:02:21.788
These ten days, 
I only thought of you.

1482
02:02:22.372 --> 02:02:26.372
You risked life to keep
your dad's head unbowed.


1483
02:02:26.788 --> 02:02:29.872
Who does such a stupid thing?

1484
02:02:29.955 --> 02:02:33.080
Head, a few degrees up or down,
what bloody difference?


1485
02:02:35.372 --> 02:02:37.747
I prayed to the Lord for you.

1486
02:02:38.122 --> 02:02:40.580
Told him, "He's one gutsy guy."

1487
02:02:40.830 --> 02:02:44.372
"Help him. Get his charges dropped."

1488
02:02:44.788 --> 02:02:46.872
The Lord said, "Bandu Boss, done!"

1489
02:02:47.997 --> 02:02:49.205
Here are the offerings.

1490
02:02:52.955 --> 02:02:54.538
Success guaranteed!

1491
02:02:54.747 --> 02:02:56.580
-Lord Ganesha...
-Glory be thine!


1492
02:02:56.705 --> 02:02:58.497
Be thine!

1493
02:02:59.247 --> 02:03:00.913
Stay in touch.

1494
02:03:01.122 --> 02:03:02.122
Let's go.

1495
02:03:08.497 --> 02:03:12.163
Get Bandu Boss teary-eyed often.

1496
02:03:12.330 --> 02:03:14.288
Free sweets will follow.

1497
02:03:15.413 --> 02:03:16.580
Sir, it's the director.

1498
02:03:20.372 --> 02:03:21.705
Yes, bro.

1499
02:03:21.788 --> 02:03:23.580
Where are you? 
We are ready to shoot.

1500
02:03:23.663 --> 02:03:26.997
Insane traffic on the highway.

1501
02:03:27.788 --> 02:03:29.830
A truck hit a car.

1502
02:03:32.163 --> 02:03:35.538
Hey, move that taxi.

1503
02:03:36.288 --> 02:03:37.705
Listen.

1504
02:03:37.955 --> 02:03:39.372
I've called the landline.

1505
02:03:42.872 --> 02:03:44.622
Landline's for all and sundry.

1506
02:03:44.705 --> 02:03:46.663
You're my bro, always call on my cell.

1507
02:03:46.747 --> 02:03:49.330
We missed the sunrise shot.

1508
02:03:49.747 --> 02:03:52.288
Shoot it at sunset.

1509
02:03:52.413 --> 02:03:54.372
The audience won't know shit.

1510
02:03:54.455 --> 02:03:57.705
<i>Now hang up or we'll miss the sunset.</i>

1511
02:03:59.163 --> 02:04:02.372
Time to introduce you to Master no. 2.

1512
02:04:03.663 --> 02:04:06.997
He'll teach you to respect work.

1513
02:04:07.372 --> 02:04:09.747
If you keep missing sunrise shoots,

1514
02:04:09.830 --> 02:04:12.288
the sun will set on your career.

1515
02:04:12.538 --> 02:04:15.413
Do good work and the press
will change its opinion, too.


1516
02:04:16.205 --> 02:04:17.872
Good work?

1517
02:04:18.205 --> 02:04:19.622
With such trashy scripts.

1518
02:04:21.580 --> 02:04:22.997
Here...

1519
02:04:24.080 --> 02:04:27.747
Kinky King, Rowdy Romeo...

1520
02:04:28.372 --> 02:04:31.788
Munnabhai MBBS, 
Punky Prince...

1521
02:04:31.872 --> 02:04:33.747
Aamir and Shah Rukh grab the best.

1522
02:04:34.122 --> 02:04:38.038
-Do you read these scripts?
-Cover to cover.


1523
02:04:38.163 --> 02:04:41.080
All read and rejected.

1524
02:04:41.538 --> 02:04:44.330
"Munnabhai MBBS." Read this one?

1525
02:04:44.455 --> 02:04:46.872
-I did.
-What's the story?


1526
02:04:49.372 --> 02:04:50.788
It's trash!

1527
02:04:52.288 --> 02:04:54.663
There's a hospital...

1528
02:04:54.788 --> 02:04:59.205
where a patient gets murdered...
every day!


1529
02:04:59.788 --> 02:05:03.663
Then kidneys are stolen.
It's a horror story.


1530
02:05:03.913 --> 02:05:05.497
I need a family film.

1531
02:05:05.788 --> 02:05:09.163
The draft I read has no murders.

1532
02:05:10.372 --> 02:05:15.580
-Why did you read it?
-I'm playing your father in this film.


1533
02:05:16.163 --> 02:05:19.663
I'll set up Master
no. 2 in your car.

1534
02:05:19.747 --> 02:05:23.580
Listen to the song
on loop at full volume.

1535
02:05:31.455 --> 02:05:34.372
<i>If you shirk from work</i>

1536
02:05:36.913 --> 02:05:39.955
<i>You get no perk, you jerk</i>

1537
02:05:40.038 --> 02:05:41.788
Turn it off!

1538
02:05:41.872 --> 02:05:44.747
It's Mr. Dutt's order to play this song
the whole month.


1539
02:05:44.830 --> 02:05:48.330
And check that you lip sync.

1540
02:05:54.788 --> 02:05:56.997
<i>If you shirk from work</i>

1541
02:05:57.080 --> 02:05:58.455
I am singing.

1542
02:05:59.663 --> 02:06:02.330
<i>You get no perk, you jerk</i>

1543
02:06:02.788 --> 02:06:05.372
<i>If duties you duck</i>
<i>You land up in muck</i>


1544
02:06:05.663 --> 02:06:08.330
<i>On bankruptcy's brink</i>
<i>Not a dime for a drink</i>


1545
02:06:08.497 --> 02:06:11.497
<i>Toil hard buddy</i>
<i>Listen to your daddy...</i>


1546
02:06:11.955 --> 02:06:13.913
-Lip sync fine?
-Yes.


1547
02:06:13.997 --> 02:06:16.872
Report to dad. 
Bloody snitch!

1548
02:06:20.538 --> 02:06:23.580
<i>Dad signed this film
after a 12 year gap</i>

1549
02:06:23.747 --> 02:06:26.205
<i>just to discipline me.</i>

1550
02:06:26.330 --> 02:06:30.830
Must an ER patient fill an admit form?

1551
02:06:35.705 --> 02:06:37.663
<i>He was always punctual on the sets.</i>

1552
02:06:37.830 --> 02:06:40.122
-Has the hero arrived?
-Yes, sir.


1553
02:06:40.705 --> 02:06:43.830
<i>So I too, had to be on time.</i>

1554
02:06:47.080 --> 02:06:49.288
Shall we rehearse?

1555
02:06:55.580 --> 02:06:57.080
Just for the shot, Dad!

1556
02:06:58.372 --> 02:07:00.997
Hey, pal. No fear, I'm here.

1557
02:07:03.330 --> 02:07:07.288
You lied to me shamelessly for ten years.

1558
02:07:12.788 --> 02:07:17.163
"Now that your father's proud,
why'd you fret?"


1559
02:07:17.372 --> 02:07:20.830
That's my dialogue.
I'm playing the father.


1560
02:07:21.372 --> 02:07:23.247
But, Father...
I couldn't become a doctor."


1561
02:07:23.330 --> 02:07:24.247
Again.

1562
02:07:24.788 --> 02:07:28.330
You lied to me shamelessly for 10 years.

1563
02:07:28.872 --> 02:07:32.663
Now that your father's proud,
why'd you fret?


1564
02:07:32.830 --> 02:07:33.830
Once again?

1565
02:07:33.997 --> 02:07:37.788
<i>Prison time was easier than this.</i>

1566
02:07:37.913 --> 02:07:40.122
<i>Dad's discipline roasted me.</i>

1567
02:07:41.122 --> 02:07:44.955
<i>But, I won't ever forget</i>
<i>that "magic hug" scene.</i>


1568
02:07:45.205 --> 02:07:47.497
Your mom gets a thousand hugs.

1569
02:07:49.080 --> 02:07:50.997
Spare one for dad.

1570
02:07:56.330 --> 02:07:59.622
<i>Neither of us heard it</i>
<i>when the director called, "Cut!"</i>


1571
02:07:59.913 --> 02:08:01.830
<i>We were weeping.</i>

1572
02:08:02.205 --> 02:08:04.913
<i>It was a lifetime since we had hugged.</i>

1573
02:08:13.497 --> 02:08:15.747
...Sanjay Dutt for "Munnabhai MBBS."

1574
02:08:20.622 --> 02:08:21.663
Go on, sonny.

1575
02:08:35.747 --> 02:08:38.830
Mr. Dutt, didn't I tell you
that Sanju will be back!


1576
02:08:39.205 --> 02:08:41.455
Really? Did you?

1577
02:08:41.538 --> 02:08:42.788
Didn't I?

1578
02:08:43.913 --> 02:08:46.622
-I told... someone.
-Who?


1579
02:08:46.788 --> 02:08:48.705
Our Associate Editor.

1580
02:08:48.955 --> 02:08:51.330
Told him to print, "Sanju will be back."

1581
02:08:51.413 --> 02:08:53.747
He must've forgotten.

1582
02:08:53.997 --> 02:08:57.288
Make it tomorrow's headline...
"Sanjay Dutt is back."


1583
02:08:59.997 --> 02:09:02.163
Without a question mark.

1584
02:09:11.205 --> 02:09:12.872
Look, Munnabhai's pop!

1585
02:09:21.872 --> 02:09:23.455
<i>Look, the terrorist's pop!</i>

1586
02:09:27.497 --> 02:09:28.538
What happened, Dad?

1587
02:09:28.622 --> 02:09:33.497
It's the second time
you've made me cry with joy.


1588
02:09:34.830 --> 02:09:39.288
<i>The first time dad cried with joy</i>
<i>was in our preview theater.</i>


1589
02:09:39.663 --> 02:09:43.997
<i>That day a headline read,</i>
<i>"RDX truck at Dutt house."</i>


1590
02:09:56.038 --> 02:10:01.622
<i>Tell the judge that you knew about</i>
<i>the bomb blast conspiracy.</i>


1591
02:10:08.038 --> 02:10:12.663
<i>The first time dad cried with joy</i>
<i>was in our preview theater.</i>


1592
02:10:12.913 --> 02:10:17.122
<i>That day a headline read,</i>
<i>"RDX truck at Dutt house."</i>


1593
02:10:17.455 --> 02:10:20.080
<i>But that's another episode.</i>

1594
02:10:20.288 --> 02:10:21.538
<i>I'll save it for another day.</i>

1595
02:10:21.788 --> 02:10:24.080
<i>Let's get back to dad.</i>

1596
02:10:24.205 --> 02:10:26.622
<i>I got another chance to make dad happy.</i>

1597
02:10:28.580 --> 02:10:31.080
<i>Dad was being honored</i>
<i>at a Consulate dinner.</i>


1598
02:10:32.372 --> 02:10:34.997
You guys never praise me.

1599
02:10:35.372 --> 02:10:37.538
So, here I am as chief guest.

1600
02:10:37.747 --> 02:10:42.038
<i>Dad was unaware, his son would</i>
<i>sing his praises tonight!</i>


1601
02:10:42.122 --> 02:10:46.122
<i>I was to make the introduction speech.</i>

1602
02:10:58.080 --> 02:10:59.247
Dad, I'll be back.

1603
02:11:00.580 --> 02:11:02.663
Sir, there's a minor problem.

1604
02:11:02.872 --> 02:11:06.830
Today's headline said, "Blast suspect
to attend diplomatic event."


1605
02:11:07.747 --> 02:11:12.080
The Embassy wanted you off the guest list.

1606
02:11:12.538 --> 02:11:15.705
We said, "That would be rude."

1607
02:11:16.372 --> 02:11:19.288
"We'll seat him away from the diplomats."

1608
02:11:32.205 --> 02:11:34.372
My speech... When's that?

1609
02:11:55.288 --> 02:11:57.913
Sonny, what's the problem?

1610
02:11:59.122 --> 02:12:02.872
I'm right here. 
Read out your speech.

1611
02:12:05.372 --> 02:12:06.872
I wanted everyone to hear it.

1612
02:12:12.497 --> 02:12:15.288
Learn to ignore such people.

1613
02:12:15.997 --> 02:12:22.163
Time for Master no. 3.
I'll set the song in your car.


1614
02:12:22.747 --> 02:12:23.788
Anand Bakshi.

1615
02:12:23.872 --> 02:12:28.455
He'll teach you to deal with humiliation.
Okay?


1616
02:12:31.038 --> 02:12:33.413
Sanju...

1617
02:12:38.830 --> 02:12:42.788
Hey, pal. No fear, I'm here!

1618
02:12:44.580 --> 02:12:45.663
Go, sleep.

1619
02:12:50.913 --> 02:12:53.830
<i>Wish I'd read him the speech,</i>

1620
02:12:54.330 --> 02:12:56.913
<i>for... the next morning,</i>
<i>he didn't wake up.</i>


1621
02:14:08.163 --> 02:14:10.038
<i>If life had a rewind button...</i>

1622
02:14:10.747 --> 02:14:13.955
<i>I'd go back and read him the speech!</i>

1623
02:14:20.788 --> 02:14:25.288
Today, I'll try the impossible...
an attempt to thank dad.


1624
02:14:25.747 --> 02:14:28.913
In the past, I never found the words.

1625
02:14:28.997 --> 02:14:33.788
To define what dad's done for me...
every word fell short.


1626
02:14:40.872 --> 02:14:42.788
<i>...a wife dying in the hospital,</i>

1627
02:14:43.372 --> 02:14:45.663
<i>a son destroyed by drugs.</i>

1628
02:14:46.163 --> 02:14:48.538
<i>Dad fought all alone.</i>

1629
02:14:48.997 --> 02:14:51.372
He's the reason I'm alive.

1630
02:14:53.330 --> 02:14:57.080
Tried to thank him then
but couldn't find the words.


1631
02:14:57.455 --> 02:15:00.080
<i>Dad walked long peace marches…</i>

1632
02:15:00.663 --> 02:15:03.497
<i>from Hiroshima to Nagasaki...</i>
<i>Mumbai to Amritsar.</i>


1633
02:15:04.413 --> 02:15:07.080
<i>But none wore off
his shoes as much as</i>

1634
02:15:07.538 --> 02:15:09.663
the jostle between courts and cops.

1635
02:15:10.455 --> 02:15:13.455
<i>Legal costs forced dad to sell his house.</i>

1636
02:15:13.622 --> 02:15:15.580
<i>Not once did he complain!</i>

1637
02:15:16.247 --> 02:15:21.997
Wanted to thank him then
but couldn't find the words.


1638
02:15:22.955 --> 02:15:27.413
Now, after a lifetime,
I've found the words.


1639
02:15:31.997 --> 02:15:36.247
You deserved a better son, Dad.

1640
02:15:37.205 --> 02:15:40.705
<i>One who'd support you... not be a burden.</i>

1641
02:15:41.663 --> 02:15:44.830
<i>One known for his honesty,</i>
<i>not his travesties.</i>


1642
02:15:45.413 --> 02:15:48.455
One more like you and less like me.

1643
02:15:55.038 --> 02:15:58.247
That son would've never loved you as much

1644
02:15:58.330 --> 02:16:00.580
as this no-good sonny does!

1645
02:16:01.122 --> 02:16:02.538
<i>I could never say it, but...</i>

1646
02:16:06.163 --> 02:16:07.580
You're my strength,

1647
02:16:08.372 --> 02:16:09.622
<i>my solace,</i>

1648
02:16:10.497 --> 02:16:11.830
my pride.

1649
02:16:11.913 --> 02:16:13.413
You're my world, Dad.

1650
02:16:18.163 --> 02:16:19.413
Love you, sonny.

1651
02:16:29.580 --> 02:16:32.038
<i>Had dad lived another year,</i>

1652
02:16:32.122 --> 02:16:35.288
<i>he'd have witnessed what he yearned for.</i>

1653
02:16:39.497 --> 02:16:42.497
...I do not find
you to be a terrorist.

1654
02:16:47.663 --> 02:16:49.580
<i>I was acquitted from the Terror Act.</i>

1655
02:16:49.955 --> 02:16:54.038
<i>I got six years under the Arms Act.</i>

1656
02:16:54.372 --> 02:16:57.372
<i>The judge clearly said</i>
<i>I was not a terrorist.</i>


1657
02:16:58.038 --> 02:16:59.288
<i>But the next morning,</i>

1658
02:16:59.455 --> 02:17:03.038
<i>no headline read "Dutt not a terrorist."</i>

1659
02:17:05.288 --> 02:17:09.622
<i>All said, "Dutt gets</i>
<i>six years in the blast case."</i>


1660
02:17:12.330 --> 02:17:14.580
Till date, I'm branded a terrorist.

1661
02:17:20.705 --> 02:17:25.538
Master no. 3 was to teach me
to deal with insults.


1662
02:17:27.163 --> 02:17:31.372
But with dad's death,
that song remains a mystery.


1663
02:17:32.122 --> 02:17:36.997
If you can crack that song, do tell.

1664
02:17:37.497 --> 02:17:41.747
Until tomorrow,
Sanju says, "Adios, amigos."


1665
02:17:57.413 --> 02:17:58.997
I want to meet Sanju.

1666
02:18:19.372 --> 02:18:20.538
How are you?

1667
02:18:20.788 --> 02:18:23.288
They don't let me step out,
the rest is fine.


1668
02:18:23.413 --> 02:18:27.538
Yeah. Sticklers for rules!
Weren't letting me in, either.


1669
02:18:28.038 --> 02:18:30.038
Missing me? Boyfriend vamoosed?

1670
02:18:32.580 --> 02:18:34.080
I'm no Pinky.

1671
02:18:36.163 --> 02:18:38.872
-You met Kamli?
-Yes.


1672
02:18:38.955 --> 02:18:40.663
In your recording, you say...

1673
02:18:41.413 --> 02:18:47.038
on the day the RDX news appeared,
your dad cried with joy.


1674
02:18:47.122 --> 02:18:48.330
Yes.

1675
02:18:48.413 --> 02:18:49.830
Kamlesh has a different version.

1676
02:18:49.913 --> 02:18:52.413
When he came to the preview theater,

1677
02:18:52.872 --> 02:18:56.330
your dad was urging you
to confess in court


1678
02:18:56.497 --> 02:18:59.330
that you knew about
the bomb blasts conspiracy.


1679
02:19:06.413 --> 02:19:07.497
The moron!

1680
02:19:08.913 --> 02:19:09.997
Get Kamli here.

1681
02:19:11.372 --> 02:19:14.913
-Tell me about it.
-No. I'll tell him directly.


1682
02:19:14.997 --> 02:19:17.747
It's hard to get permission.

1683
02:19:21.747 --> 02:19:24.372
Remember this number, 88.0.

1684
02:19:24.622 --> 02:19:26.372
-What's that?
-A radio frequency.


1685
02:19:26.455 --> 02:19:28.663
There's an FM mic in our studio.

1686
02:19:29.205 --> 02:19:34.580
Park close to the prison walls
and tune in.


1687
02:19:37.747 --> 02:19:38.872
Kamlesh won't come.

1688
02:19:40.455 --> 02:19:45.538
Tell him... 6th June. 
He won't refuse.

1689
02:19:48.705 --> 02:19:52.788
It's his dad's birthday.
Bloody emotional blackmailer!


1690
02:19:53.330 --> 02:19:54.455
Will you come?

1691
02:20:28.997 --> 02:20:31.080
<i>Howdy, Yerwada!</i>

1692
02:20:31.205 --> 02:20:35.288
<i>This is your buddy, Sanju!</i>

1693
02:20:38.788 --> 02:20:41.747
Today's topic is "friendship."

1694
02:20:42.163 --> 02:20:44.288
My best friend was Kamli.

1695
02:20:45.205 --> 02:20:49.122
Great guy. But fell prey to drugs.

1696
02:20:49.997 --> 02:20:52.913
<i>No... not the psychotropic drugs.</i>

1697
02:20:53.330 --> 02:20:59.913
But the ones that are slid
under our doors, daily.


1698
02:21:00.747 --> 02:21:02.913
<i>We have them with our morning tea.</i>

1699
02:21:03.413 --> 02:21:06.747
Drugs called "News."

1700
02:21:07.622 --> 02:21:09.413
<i>These drugs are sold on TV too.</i>

1701
02:21:09.747 --> 02:21:14.122
Haven't you heard those
